					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I've used CA65 for a while.  Only recently I'd written a little test program in C, it compiled and worked once I stopped trying to use functions like printf (I guess the NES library is currently broke or unwritten).
<br />
<br />Mixing asm and C should work fine.  It's probably best to keep your asm away from the compiler, because it'll try to optimize it.  So I'd bring it together during assembly or linking.
<br />
<br />Also, a 4MHZ Z80 is probably slower than a 1.79Mhz 6502.  Z80 uses a lot of clock cycles, while the 6502 completes many instructions in 2 - 4 clocks.  But they're pretty close in speed, it depends on the code.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

